      "span_text": "This inherent flexibility may facilitate the sequestration of sharply bent, hooked juxtapositions of catenated DNA strands between nucleosomes (Fig 6) .  have proposed that type-2 topoisomerases use the local information at helix-helix juxtapositions to distinguish entanglements from two helices that are juxtaposed but not entangled."
